wiki.content: “CHURCH GIRL” is an infusion of R&B, Gospel, Chicago Hip-Hop, & Southern Hip-Hop. The elements of R&B and Gospel shine through the verses and sample of “Center Of Thy Will” by The Clark Sisters. While the Southern Hip-Hop influence are found in the catchy chorus & post-chorus similar to 7/11 off Beyoncé’s 2013 Self-Titled. The Southern Hip-Hop instrumentation is further evident in the sample of “Drag Rap” by The Showboys that appears throughout the chorus & post-chorus. Chicago Hip-Hop elements are delivered in classic No I.D. fashion taking an 80’s gospel track, looping & flipping the track to provide a rebirth and modern interpretation on Beyoncé’s RENAISSANCE. This also marks the third collaboration with No I.D. and first as a lead artist after “Family Feud” with JAY-Z & “See Me Now” with Kanye West, Big Sean & Charlie Wilson. Read more on Last.fm.
